## Part 1: Brand Manifest & Style Anchor Block (Steps 1–2)

### 1A — Master Style Anchor Block

Every image and video prompt must include this block verbatim. Define it once in Step 1 and inject it unchanged into all downstream prompts.

```
[Style Anchor: <Brand> Manifest v1.0]
[Camera: <camera body, e.g. ARRI Alexa Mini LF, Cooke S7i Prime 35mm T2.0>]
[Lens Protocol: <DoF range, e.g. f/2.8–f/4.0, anamorphic 1.8x squeeze for horizontal flares>]
[Lighting: <color temp + key style, e.g. 3200K–4200K mixed, high-contrast noir key with negative fill>]
[Palette: <HEX values with labels, e.g. #0A0A0C (void black), #2C2C2E (brushed titanium)>]
[Framing: <occupancy rule, e.g. subject occupancy ≤35%, rule-of-thirds negative space>]
[Texture Guardrails: <material constraints, e.g. zero specular bloom on carbon fiber>]
[Temporal Lock: 24fps native, 180° shutter simulation, zero motion blur on static elements]
```

**Checklist before injecting:**
- [ ] HEX palette defined (minimum 3 colors)
- [ ] Camera body + lens spec locked
- [ ] Lighting temperature range specified
- [ ] Subject occupancy ≤35% (prevents hero shot crowding)
- [ ] Texture guardrails include "zero specular bloom" for metallic/reflective surfaces

