### 1B — 15-Second Dual-Column Ad Script

Structure the script as a dual-column table with timecode brackets.

| Timecode | Visual & Motion Cues | Voiceover (Punctuation-Scripted) |
|----------|---------------------|----------------------------------|
| 0s–4s | MACRO HERO: Extreme close-up on [hero texture]. Rack focus from [element A] to [element B]. Zero camera shake. | [Brand]... is not a [category]. It is a [statement]— |
| 4s–9s | ARCHITECTURAL REVEAL: Low-angle dolly glide reveals full silhouette in [environment]. Subject static; camera moves constant velocity. | ...for the [target persona]. Who values [brand value]... over [contrast]. |
| 9s–12s | HUMAN INTEGRATION: [Human element] interacts with product. Gentle push-in maintains eye-line. | [Benefit]... engineered. For the [context]— |
| 12s–15s | FINAL LOCK: Wide silhouette against [backdrop]. Brand signature [action]. Fade to black + logotype. | ...[closing line]. |

**Punctuation rules for voiceover scripts:**
- `,` = brief inhalation pause
- `.` = full pitch drop + resting breath
- `...` = slow atmospheric drawl
- `—` = intentional emphasis break

