## Part 2: Downstream Engine Prompts (Steps 3, 4, 6)

### 2A — Fused Image Prompt (Step 3: Flux Pro / Midjourney v6.5)

```
"[State] <static anchor description — no motion>. [Subject Motion] None — static anchor frame. [Camera Motion] None — pristine Frame 1 asset. [Guardrails] Zero motion blur, photorealistic I2V anchor, high temporal stability, zero geometry drift, subject occupancy ≤35%, rule-of-thirds negative space. [Style Anchor: <Brand> Manifest v1.0] <inject full Style Anchor Block verbatim>."
```

**Critical**: The image must be engineered as an I2V (image-to-video) anchor — not just a beautiful still. Temporal stability and zero geometry drift are non-negotiable keywords.

---

### 2B — Fused Motion Video Prompt (Step 4)

Use the **Dual-Vector structure** — Subject Motion and Camera Motion must always be in separate clauses:

```
"[State] <repeat static anchor from Step 3>. [Subject Motion] <explicit physics verbs at specific velocity, e.g. smooth linear forward translation at 15km/h equivalent>. [Camera Motion] <cinematic technical term, e.g. motorized dolly left-to-right tracking glide at constant velocity>. [Guardrails] Zero camera shake, 24fps native temporal stability, zero geometry drift on <key textures>. [Style Anchor: <Brand> Manifest v1.0] (injected verbatim). [Audio Specification: High-fidelity diegetic sound only. <foley details>. Zero background music — pure foley for single-pass sync.]"
```

**Engine Selection Matrix:**

| Engine | Strength | Best Use Case | Tip |
|--------|----------|--------------|-----|
| Kling 3.0 | Micro-specular physics, human anatomy | Macro detail, human integration, physics-heavy motion | Pair physics-heavy subject with simple camera moves |
| Veo 3.1 | Cinematic camera blocking, spatial continuity | Architectural reveals, complex camera terminology | Leverage complex camera terms; keep subject motion moderate |
| Runway Gen-4.5 | Motion Brush, abstract motion | Experimental/stylized transitions | Use Motion Brush + abstract verbs; avoid photorealistic expectations |

**Operational Rules — Video Prompting:**

| Rule | If Violated | Fix |
|------|-------------|-----|
| Never set UI camera controls opposite to text (e.g. UI="Zoom In" + text="crane-down") | Temporal matrix tear → glitching, double heads | Align UI controls with prompt language before render |
| Avoid vague directives ("fast action", "crazy movement") | Unpredictable noise output | Use explicit technical language: "linear translation at 15km/h equivalent" |
| Always separate Subject Motion and Camera Motion into distinct clauses | Model rotates objects instead of moving camera | Use bracketed clauses: `[Subject Motion]... [Camera Motion]...` |

