### 2C — Udio Audio Meta-Tag Prompt (Step 6)

Use **bracketed descriptors only** — never conversational sentences:

```
[Style: <genre 1>, <genre 2>, <genre 3>, <BPM> BPM]
[Instrumentation: <instrument 1>, <instrument 2>, <instrument 3 — max 3–4 layers for commercial tracks>]
[Structure: Intro: <description>], [Build: <description>], [Drop: <description>], [Outro: <description>]
[Mixing/Production: Tight side-chain compression (-6dB to -9dB dip for voiceover pocket), <additional specs>]
[Brand Alignment: <brand name + key brand values>]
```

**Music prompting rules:**
- Use technical genre names + specific instrument names (e.g. "felt piano", "analog synthesizer") — not mood words like "luxury" or "epic"
- Limit to 3–4 core instrument layers maximum for commercial background tracks
- Always include side-chain compression spec so voiceover remains audible: `-6dB to -9dB`
- Udio > Suno for premium/luxury/cinematic scores; Suno for upbeat pop/vocal-forward tracks

