## Part 3: Operational Guardrails & Pipeline Failure Points

### 3A — Critical Failure Points (Steps 3→4 Boundary)

| Failure Point | Risk | Engineering Solution |
|---------------|------|----------------------|
| **Style Anchor Drift** | Image has full Style Anchor; video model receives truncated prompt → color grade shift, texture loss | **PROMPT HASH VERIFICATION**: Auto-extract `[Style Anchor]` from Step 3 metadata; inject verbatim into Step 4. Use MD5 checksum to verify byte-for-byte identity. Halt pipeline if mismatch >0%. |
| **Temporal Physics Inconsistency** | Static mist density 0.3 in image; video generates mist at 0.7 during motion → visual discontinuity | **PHYSICS PARAMETER LOCKS**: Embed in `[Guardrails]`: `volumetric mist displacement coefficient = 0.3–0.5, linear correlation with vehicle velocity`. Use Kling 3.0 physics bias mode or Houdini pre-render as ControlNet reference. |
| **Audio-Visual Desync (Single-Pass Foley)** | Vehicle moves at 15km/h in video; audio transformer generates motor hum at 30km/h pitch → Doppler mismatch | **VELOCITY-TO-FREQUENCY MAPPING**: Bind in `[Audio Specification]`: `motor hum fundamental frequency = 42Hz @ 15km/h, linear pitch shift +2.3Hz per 1km/h`. Enforce foley-only in single-pass; layer background score separately in post. |

---

### 3B — Single-Pass Audio Generation: Critical Constraint

> **Never mix foley + music in single-pass generation.**

- **Single-pass only for**: diegetic foley (footsteps, impacts, motor hum, environmental sound)
- **Split pipeline (Step 6 separately) for**: music, voiceover, non-diegetic audio

If foley and music are requested together in single-pass, the audio transformer warps foley to match the music's rhythmic structure → corrupted diegetic sync.

**Single-Pass Audio Specification block format:**
```
[Audio Specification: High-fidelity diegetic sound. <describe sound physics explicitly, e.g. sub-40Hz motor hum with subtle coil whine, tire friction on polished concrete, distant ambient bed>. Zero background music — pure foley audio.]
```

---

### 3C — Post-Production Assembly Checklist

| Step | Action | Purpose |
|------|--------|---------|
| 1. Frame Alignment | Verify Shot N end-frame lighting matches Shot N+1 start-frame shadow direction | Prevents jarring exposure jumps between I2V outputs |
| 2. Speed Ramping | Apply 90% speed ramp to emotional hold shots | Smooths DiT micro-jitter |
| 3. Audio Design | Layer sub-40Hz ambient bed + diegetic foley | Grounds AI visual physics in real-world sensory cues |
| 4. Voiceover Side-Chain | Side-chain music track: dip -6dB to -9dB whenever voiceover amplitude registers | Prevents voiceover burial |
| 5. Final Conform | Export ProRes 422, apply brand LUT | Locks brand DNA: color grade, zero noise |

